1
00:00:00,090 --> 00:00:00,930
Want to be rich?

2
00:00:00,930 --> 00:00:02,010
Follow your passion

3
00:00:02,010 --> 00:00:03,930
and you'll never work a day in your life.

4
00:00:03,930 --> 00:00:06,750
This is terrible advice.

5
00:00:06,750 --> 00:00:09,750
So is manifest your success, slow down,

6
00:00:09,750 --> 00:00:12,060
follow the rules and learn to compromise.

7
00:00:12,060 --> 00:00:14,400
In fact, this advice is
the complete opposite

8
00:00:14,400 --> 00:00:16,950
of what actually leads to real success.

9
00:00:16,950 --> 00:00:19,140
It's almost like these well known sayings

10
00:00:19,140 --> 00:00:20,790
are designed to make you feel good,

11
00:00:20,790 --> 00:00:23,460
but ultimately keep you poor.

12
00:00:23,460 --> 00:00:26,100
I'm going to upset a
lot of online gurus here

13
00:00:26,100 --> 00:00:27,180
with this video,

14
00:00:27,180 --> 00:00:29,550
but if you are serious
about becoming rich,

15
00:00:29,550 --> 00:00:31,770
then the people spouting this nonsense

16
00:00:31,770 --> 00:00:33,840
are completely wasting your time.

17
00:00:33,840 --> 00:00:36,450
Most of these people have
never actually made millions

18
00:00:36,450 --> 00:00:40,230
or even worse they have, but
by pretending to be rich.

19
00:00:40,230 --> 00:00:41,730
Look, I've been there and done it

20
00:00:41,730 --> 00:00:43,500
and made a lot of money in the process.

21
00:00:43,500 --> 00:00:46,380
So here's my five step anti-guru formula

22
00:00:46,380 --> 00:00:48,810
which will actually help you become rich.

23
00:00:48,810 --> 00:00:52,170
Step one, don't follow your passion.

24
00:00:52,170 --> 00:00:54,600
Right, let's clear
something up right away.

25
00:00:54,600 --> 00:00:56,760
Often when I say don't follow your passion

26
00:00:56,760 --> 00:00:58,470
lots of people jump to the conclusion

27
00:00:58,470 --> 00:01:00,900
that I'm telling people to
just focus on the money.

28
00:01:00,900 --> 00:01:02,220
This is not the case.

29
00:01:02,220 --> 00:01:03,750
I just fundamentally disagree

30
00:01:03,750 --> 00:01:05,580
with the follow your passion advice.

31
00:01:05,580 --> 00:01:06,720
It's very unclear,

32
00:01:06,720 --> 00:01:08,190
it's highly self-centered,

33
00:01:08,190 --> 00:01:10,410
and very impractical for many people.

34
00:01:10,410 --> 00:01:12,660
Let's break down the issues one by one.

35
00:01:12,660 --> 00:01:16,830
Firstly, the actual meaning of
the word passion is unclear.

36
00:01:16,830 --> 00:01:18,690
It's just one of those fluffy words

37
00:01:18,690 --> 00:01:20,909
that has no real universal definition.

38
00:01:20,909 --> 00:01:24,420
I suppose the best place to
start is the Oxford Dictionary,

39
00:01:24,420 --> 00:01:26,400
which says passion is a strong

40
00:01:26,400 --> 00:01:28,410
and barely controllable emotion.

41
00:01:28,410 --> 00:01:29,250
See what I mean?

42
00:01:29,250 --> 00:01:32,070
It's extremely open for interpretation.

43
00:01:32,070 --> 00:01:33,690
This makes it hard to tell the difference

44
00:01:33,690 --> 00:01:36,210
between an impulsive short-lived interest

45
00:01:36,210 --> 00:01:38,220
and a possible route to success.

46
00:01:38,220 --> 00:01:40,050
The other interesting thing about passion

47
00:01:40,050 --> 00:01:43,620
is that it fades, especially
if you turn it into a job.

48
00:01:43,620 --> 00:01:45,780
This is because once you
get paid for something

49
00:01:45,780 --> 00:01:47,370
that you used to do for fun,

50
00:01:47,370 --> 00:01:50,100
it becomes an obligation
rather than a choice.

51
00:01:50,100 --> 00:01:53,730
Once it fades, another
passion will probably pop up.

52
00:01:53,730 --> 00:01:57,570
Now say you follow that new
passion and abandon the old one.

53
00:01:57,570 --> 00:01:59,820
You've gotta start again from ground zero.

54
00:01:59,820 --> 00:02:01,290
Now that's fine once or twice

55
00:02:01,290 --> 00:02:02,940
and I've got friends that have done it.

56
00:02:02,940 --> 00:02:04,440
But to become rich,

57
00:02:04,440 --> 00:02:06,780
you need to get really good at something

58
00:02:06,780 --> 00:02:09,954
and the only way to do this is
through hours of dedication.

59
00:02:09,954 --> 00:02:13,920
Secondly, following your
passion is all about you

60
00:02:13,920 --> 00:02:14,760
and not others.

61
00:02:14,760 --> 00:02:17,010
The true secret to becoming rich

62
00:02:17,010 --> 00:02:20,160
is to provide what the market
wants, not what you want.

63
00:02:20,160 --> 00:02:22,758
Say you were extremely
passionate about paper airplanes,

64
00:02:22,758 --> 00:02:25,050
it's gonna be really hard getting rich

65
00:02:25,050 --> 00:02:26,820
doing this as a full-time job

66
00:02:26,820 --> 00:02:28,590
because the market is so small.

67
00:02:28,590 --> 00:02:29,970
That's why you have to make sure

68
00:02:29,970 --> 00:02:32,190
there's an actual demand for what you do.

69
00:02:32,190 --> 00:02:34,740
Otherwise, you can follow
your passion all you want,

70
00:02:34,740 --> 00:02:36,300
but it won't make you wealthy.

71
00:02:36,300 --> 00:02:39,660
The only person that cares
about your feelings is you

72
00:02:39,660 --> 00:02:40,830
and maybe your family.

73
00:02:40,830 --> 00:02:44,280
Thirdly, the most important
issue of them all.

74
00:02:44,280 --> 00:02:46,230
Most people don't have a passion.

75
00:02:46,230 --> 00:02:49,110
Look, I'm sick of all
this stereotypical advice.

76
00:02:49,110 --> 00:02:50,940
Just do something for long enough,

77
00:02:50,940 --> 00:02:52,530
this will lead to you becoming better

78
00:02:52,530 --> 00:02:54,330
and ultimately you'll start to love it.

79
00:02:54,330 --> 00:02:57,750
I know people that have worked
in an office job for 30 years

80
00:02:57,750 --> 00:03:01,050
and while good at it,
they absolutely hate it.

81
00:03:01,050 --> 00:03:03,270
So with that said, I'm gonna amend

82
00:03:03,270 --> 00:03:06,900
follow your passion to what
Mark Cuban once suggested,

83
00:03:06,900 --> 00:03:08,850
follow your effort.

84
00:03:08,850 --> 00:03:11,220
Emotions are unreliable.

85
00:03:11,220 --> 00:03:13,290
Cold hard facts aren't.

86
00:03:13,290 --> 00:03:15,420
So if you really want to become rich,

87
00:03:15,420 --> 00:03:17,724
then closely track where you freely choose

88
00:03:17,724 --> 00:03:20,400
to apply your time and pursue that.

89
00:03:20,400 --> 00:03:22,890
Time is your most valuable asset.

90
00:03:22,890 --> 00:03:24,540
You can't make any more of it.

91
00:03:24,540 --> 00:03:26,280
You dunno how much you have left

92
00:03:26,280 --> 00:03:27,810
and you can never buy it back.

93
00:03:27,810 --> 00:03:29,190
This means that tracking what you do

94
00:03:29,190 --> 00:03:31,290
in your free time is a fantastic way

95
00:03:31,290 --> 00:03:33,600
of identifying what you
actually care about,

96
00:03:33,600 --> 00:03:36,210
but this is where you can fall

97
00:03:36,210 --> 00:03:38,850
for the next bit of bad advice.

98
00:03:38,850 --> 00:03:42,570
Step two, don't manifest success.

99
00:03:42,570 --> 00:03:44,910
I'm sick and tired of
these people talking about

100
00:03:44,910 --> 00:03:47,760
how manifestation changed their lives.

101
00:03:47,760 --> 00:03:49,170
When you followed your effort,

102
00:03:49,170 --> 00:03:50,760
the most dangerous thing you can do

103
00:03:50,760 --> 00:03:53,610
is stop taking action
and start manifesting.

104
00:03:53,610 --> 00:03:56,160
I now have everything I ever wanted.

105
00:03:56,160 --> 00:03:59,820
But I'll let you into a
secret, I didn't manifest once.

106
00:03:59,820 --> 00:04:01,410
Before you jump to the conclusion

107
00:04:01,410 --> 00:04:04,770
that I'm saying self-belief
is useless, hear me out,

108
00:04:04,770 --> 00:04:06,690
my main problem with manifestation

109
00:04:06,690 --> 00:04:09,960
of fake guru, survivor bias,
and false expectations.

110
00:04:09,960 --> 00:04:12,000
It's no secret the fake gurus

111
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:14,580
talk about manifestation nonstop.

112
00:04:14,580 --> 00:04:16,020
Why do you think that is?

113
00:04:16,020 --> 00:04:18,120
It's because it sells false hope,

114
00:04:18,120 --> 00:04:20,250
which is a very profitable product.

115
00:04:20,250 --> 00:04:21,990
They suck people in with the promise

116
00:04:21,990 --> 00:04:23,610
that if they think hard enough,

117
00:04:23,610 --> 00:04:26,550
then everything will be given
to them on a silver platter.

118
00:04:26,550 --> 00:04:29,220
It's also very easy for them
to blame their customers

119
00:04:29,220 --> 00:04:31,350
when their poorly made online course

120
00:04:31,350 --> 00:04:33,420
doesn't deliver the promise results.

121
00:04:33,420 --> 00:04:35,100
I can't tell you the amount of times

122
00:04:35,100 --> 00:04:36,540
I've seen people complain

123
00:04:36,540 --> 00:04:38,130
after buying one of these courses.

124
00:04:38,130 --> 00:04:40,920
When they say something like,
"This didn't work for me."

125
00:04:40,920 --> 00:04:42,750
Instead of receiving a refund,

126
00:04:42,750 --> 00:04:44,317
they normally get an answer like,

127
00:04:44,317 --> 00:04:47,190
"It's because you didn't
manifest hard enough."

128
00:04:47,190 --> 00:04:49,710
This is exactly how most scams work.

129
00:04:49,710 --> 00:04:51,420
They blame the customer.

130
00:04:51,420 --> 00:04:54,180
It's not just these fake
gurus pushing this bad advice,

131
00:04:54,180 --> 00:04:56,670
it's also the people that
it happened to work for.

132
00:04:56,670 --> 00:04:59,370
One of the most famous
examples is Jim Carey,

133
00:04:59,370 --> 00:05:02,490
who famously wrote himself
a $10 million check

134
00:05:02,490 --> 00:05:04,380
before he achieved success.

135
00:05:04,380 --> 00:05:07,207
Sometime later, he found
how he was cast in the movie

136
00:05:07,207 --> 00:05:10,950
"Dumb and Dumber" for you
guessed it, $10 million.

137
00:05:10,950 --> 00:05:13,230
A lot of people point
to this as an example

138
00:05:13,230 --> 00:05:15,240
of manifestation working.

139
00:05:15,240 --> 00:05:16,920
However, this is far more likely

140
00:05:16,920 --> 00:05:20,130
due to the hundreds of other
things Jim Carey was doing.

141
00:05:20,130 --> 00:05:22,350
There are probably
thousands of other stories

142
00:05:22,350 --> 00:05:24,850
just like this one that
didn't have a happy ending,

143
00:05:24,850 --> 00:05:27,690
but we'll never get to hear about those.

144
00:05:27,690 --> 00:05:30,960
It just sets people up for
unrealistic expectation

145
00:05:30,960 --> 00:05:33,420
and promotes the idea
that you can do nothing

146
00:05:33,420 --> 00:05:34,380
and get results.

147
00:05:34,380 --> 00:05:36,090
So once you're following your effort,

148
00:05:36,090 --> 00:05:38,460
instead of spending your time manifesting,

149
00:05:38,460 --> 00:05:41,160
you need to get your head
down and develop grits.

150
00:05:41,160 --> 00:05:44,160
This means instead of giving
up when something goes wrong,

151
00:05:44,160 --> 00:05:47,490
you see it as an opportunity
to learn and stay committed

152
00:05:47,490 --> 00:05:49,680
to the long-term pursuit of your goals.

153
00:05:49,680 --> 00:05:52,350
By developing grit, you
can build a resilience

154
00:05:52,350 --> 00:05:56,430
and perseverance necessary
to achieve last in success.

155
00:05:56,430 --> 00:05:57,570
Once you do this,

156
00:05:57,570 --> 00:06:00,060
you'll have results that
will boost your confidence

157
00:06:00,060 --> 00:06:02,910
and self-belief, which
is 10 times more powerful

158
00:06:02,910 --> 00:06:04,620
than standing in front of the mirror

159
00:06:04,620 --> 00:06:07,110
and repeating that you're
gonna be rich one day.

160
00:06:07,110 --> 00:06:08,940
When you manage to get to this stage,

161
00:06:08,940 --> 00:06:11,790
you'll probably notice people
starting to pull you back.

162
00:06:11,790 --> 00:06:14,340
Which leads me to step three,

163
00:06:14,340 --> 00:06:15,810
don't slow down.

164
00:06:15,810 --> 00:06:17,430
Whoever tells you to slow down

165
00:06:17,430 --> 00:06:20,010
is trying to stop you becoming successful.

166
00:06:20,010 --> 00:06:23,010
Moving swiftly led me
to quicker solutions,

167
00:06:23,010 --> 00:06:25,710
which resulted in me
making a lot more money.

168
00:06:25,710 --> 00:06:26,760
But before you say it,

169
00:06:26,760 --> 00:06:28,620
I'm not saying you shouldn't be patient.

170
00:06:28,620 --> 00:06:30,300
There is a huge difference.

171
00:06:30,300 --> 00:06:31,260
Let me explain.

172
00:06:31,260 --> 00:06:33,690
You need to have a sense
of urgency in your life.

173
00:06:33,690 --> 00:06:35,610
After all, we're only getting older

174
00:06:35,610 --> 00:06:37,830
and your brain is only getting slower.

175
00:06:37,830 --> 00:06:39,840
So its best to push yourself now

176
00:06:39,840 --> 00:06:41,550
while you have the energy to do it.

177
00:06:41,550 --> 00:06:44,520
Small actions lead to big outcomes

178
00:06:44,520 --> 00:06:46,680
and the small things that you do each day

179
00:06:46,680 --> 00:06:49,650
build on each other
and compound over time.

180
00:06:49,650 --> 00:06:51,420
That's why you should take action now.

181
00:06:51,420 --> 00:06:54,270
Phrases like, "If you
build it, they will come,"

182
00:06:54,270 --> 00:06:56,760
are really misguiding as they suggest that

183
00:06:56,760 --> 00:06:59,220
if you wait, then things will work out.

184
00:06:59,220 --> 00:07:00,053
I get it.

185
00:07:00,053 --> 00:07:01,260
Who doesn't want to believe

186
00:07:01,260 --> 00:07:03,090
that when you build a great product

187
00:07:03,090 --> 00:07:05,430
or offer a fantastic service,

188
00:07:05,430 --> 00:07:08,070
as long as you wait long
enough, you'll become rich.

189
00:07:08,070 --> 00:07:10,980
The truth is the world
doesn't work like that.

190
00:07:10,980 --> 00:07:13,950
If you sit back and wait for
the money to start flowing in,

191
00:07:13,950 --> 00:07:15,510
then it probably never will.

192
00:07:15,510 --> 00:07:17,970
Taking your time will lead to you missing

193
00:07:17,970 --> 00:07:19,530
your golden opportunity.

194
00:07:19,530 --> 00:07:22,080
So don't listen to the people
that are holding you back.

195
00:07:22,080 --> 00:07:23,910
If something needs to be done, do it.

196
00:07:23,910 --> 00:07:25,410
There's no point waiting.

197
00:07:25,410 --> 00:07:27,570
You need to move swiftly
with your actions,

198
00:07:27,570 --> 00:07:29,460
but be patient with the results.

199
00:07:29,460 --> 00:07:31,830
However, if you always do everything

200
00:07:31,830 --> 00:07:33,690
the way other people expect,

201
00:07:33,690 --> 00:07:36,360
then you will never reach
your true potential.

202
00:07:36,360 --> 00:07:38,760
Which leads me onto step four,

203
00:07:38,760 --> 00:07:40,380
don't follow the rules.

204
00:07:40,380 --> 00:07:43,295
On my score report, it would
always say the same thing.

205
00:07:43,295 --> 00:07:47,070
Mark has potential, but
he's highly disruptive.

206
00:07:47,070 --> 00:07:48,600
I used to get told off for that.

207
00:07:48,600 --> 00:07:51,870
However, if the same thing was
written on "Times" magazine

208
00:07:51,870 --> 00:07:54,660
with a big picture of me
plastered on the front,

209
00:07:54,660 --> 00:07:56,460
then I'll be celebrated for it.

210
00:07:56,460 --> 00:07:58,770
The truth is, if you
do everything the same

211
00:07:58,770 --> 00:08:02,430
as everyone else, then you
end up with the same results.

212
00:08:02,430 --> 00:08:04,830
I like to think of it
as being a fisherman.

213
00:08:04,830 --> 00:08:07,320
And instead of fishing
where everyone else does,

214
00:08:07,320 --> 00:08:09,300
you decide to go off the beaten track

215
00:08:09,300 --> 00:08:10,710
and find a hidden lake.

216
00:08:10,710 --> 00:08:12,780
That's why when I opened my first shop,

217
00:08:12,780 --> 00:08:15,660
I went back to my disruptive tendencies

218
00:08:15,660 --> 00:08:18,000
and racked my brains for whatever I could

219
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:20,400
to do a bit differently
from my competitors.

220
00:08:20,400 --> 00:08:23,670
That's when I came up with
this genius marketing strategy

221
00:08:23,670 --> 00:08:25,860
to establish myself in the area.

222
00:08:25,860 --> 00:08:28,650
In the dead of night, I
went around a neighborhood

223
00:08:28,650 --> 00:08:31,290
with hundreds of signs and cable ties.

224
00:08:31,290 --> 00:08:32,520
I stuck these signs up,

225
00:08:32,520 --> 00:08:35,850
directing people towards my
shop from all directions.

226
00:08:35,850 --> 00:08:37,200
It were at wonders.

227
00:08:37,200 --> 00:08:40,350
About three months later, I got
a visit from the authorities

228
00:08:40,350 --> 00:08:42,360
who asked me to remove the signs.

229
00:08:42,360 --> 00:08:45,960
However, by that point,
they'd done their intended job

230
00:08:45,960 --> 00:08:48,772
and now word of mouth was
already spreading about my shop.

231
00:08:48,772 --> 00:08:51,690
You are competing against
a lot more people.

232
00:08:51,690 --> 00:08:52,920
By breaking the rules,

233
00:08:52,920 --> 00:08:55,950
you can quite often find a
lot of new opportunities.

234
00:08:55,950 --> 00:08:58,950
Now you've followed your
effort, developed grit,

235
00:08:58,950 --> 00:09:00,270
and broken the rules,

236
00:09:00,270 --> 00:09:03,240
there is one more advice
trap you can fall into.

237
00:09:03,240 --> 00:09:06,930
Step five, don't learn to compromise.

238
00:09:06,930 --> 00:09:09,600
People say compromising is great.

239
00:09:09,600 --> 00:09:11,520
You need to be able to find common ground

240
00:09:11,520 --> 00:09:13,410
and negotiate with people in life

241
00:09:13,410 --> 00:09:14,580
so that you can all get along

242
00:09:14,580 --> 00:09:16,320
and come to the best solutions.

243
00:09:16,320 --> 00:09:17,910
No, it's not.

244
00:09:17,910 --> 00:09:19,950
That's not what compromising is.

245
00:09:19,950 --> 00:09:22,260
Compromise is about reaching a settlement

246
00:09:22,260 --> 00:09:25,080
that is often lower than the
standards you would expect,

247
00:09:25,080 --> 00:09:27,330
whether or not it feels
the right thing to do.

248
00:09:27,330 --> 00:09:30,330
I see compromise as another
word for mediocracy.

249
00:09:30,330 --> 00:09:32,010
I get you may be thinking,

250
00:09:32,010 --> 00:09:34,350
if you go through life
not listening to others,

251
00:09:34,350 --> 00:09:36,930
then you're gonna come
across as a bit of a dick,

252
00:09:36,930 --> 00:09:38,370
and I completely agree.

253
00:09:38,370 --> 00:09:40,920
Other people may have
ideas and perspectives

254
00:09:40,920 --> 00:09:42,420
that you haven't considered.

255
00:09:42,420 --> 00:09:44,280
Learning from them is vital,

256
00:09:44,280 --> 00:09:46,890
but that doesn't mean
you have to compromise.

257
00:09:46,890 --> 00:09:47,910
There's a huge difference

258
00:09:47,910 --> 00:09:49,800
between someone that
doesn't listen to others

259
00:09:49,800 --> 00:09:51,510
because of their huge ego

260
00:09:51,510 --> 00:09:54,180
and someone that listens
and weighs up their options.

261
00:09:54,180 --> 00:09:56,460
